</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Berlusconi government is due to give its long-delayed approval today for
the appointment of Mr Vincenzo Desario as director-general of the Bank of
Italy. On October 18 the central bank's governing council named Mr Desario,
junior of the two deputy directors, to replace Mr Lamberto Dini, who became
