<HEADLINE>
FT  03 NOV 94 / Commodities and Agriculture: Jamaica sells banana farms
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CANUTE JAMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KINGSTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Jamaican government has divested two of the island's largest banana
farms to Fyffes of the UK and Producers Group, a local company. The
companies, which market all of Jamaica's export bananas, paid USDollars 6m
for a 95 per cent interest in the two farms, with Fyffes being the minority
partner.
The government is expecting improved production of bananas with the
divestment. Mr Seymour Mullings, the agriculture minister, said exports of
the fruit next year should reach 105,000 tonnes, which is the island's quota
to the European Union. This year's exports are projected at 85,000 tonnes.
Meanwhile, the marketing of bananas produced in the Windward Islands is
being restructured with the creation of a new marketing company.
