<HEADLINE>
FT  03 NOV 94 / Holman Hunt replica sold for Pounds 1.87m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SUSAN MOORE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A quarter-size replica of William Holman Hunt's 'The Shadow of Death'
realised Pounds 1.87m at Sotheby's, London, setting a new auction record for
a pre-Raphaelite picture and the third highest auction price for a Victorian
painting. The replica was made by Hunt for the use of the engraver.
The same bidder also paid Pounds 166,500 for DG Rossetti's portrait in
chalks of his sister, the poet Christina Rossetti.
London dealers McConnal Mason, who have frequently acted for composer Sir
Andrew Lloyd Webber, paid a record Pounds 551,500 for Poynter's highly
erotic sirens of 'The Cave of the Storm Nymphs' although the painting was
last seen at auction six years ago when it fetched Pounds 440,000. Mr David
Mason also bid a record Pounds 168,700 for the Pre-Raphaelite James
Collinson's 'The Emigration Scheme'.
Albert Moore's tribute to the art of music fared less well and was bought in
at Pounds 500,000. The sale totalled Pounds 4,520,849 with 79.5 per cent
sold by value.
</TEXT>
