FT  03 NOV 94 / Reserves rise
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The UK's official reserves rose by an underlying Dollars 41m in October. The
underlying figure excludes, among other things, the proceeds of an issue of
Treasury notes, denominated in European currency units (Ecus), which raised
Dollars 536m. In overall terms, the reserves rose by Dollars 49m, bringing
the total to Dollars 43.98bn.
