<HEADLINE>
FT  03 NOV 94 / World News in Brief: Renault sets share price for
privatisation issue
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Renault shares will go on sale to the public today at FFr165 (Dollars 32.18)
a share, valuing the company at slightly under FFr40bn (Pounds 4.7bn). The
state is selling nearly 30 per cent of Renault's capital but will retain a
50.1 per cent stake. The sale to institutions will end today while the
public offering will last until next Thursday.
